name: reaction confusion
description: sigil 8. any algorithm hunting digital nomad will admit we all go through a reaction diffusion phase. it’s inevitable: a simple equation that results in endless natural patterns. some rookies believe that because a visual looks like a zebra’s skin or coral reef, the source code must function similarly to the biological process that forms said patterns. it doesn't. many refer to this error as "reaction confusion." collect to attract insight. inscribed by tenorless circa 2021 // genesis collection
